3. **Theoretical PM-Prediction Comparison**: Develop a theoretical model for the PM-expected power spectrum by applying a grid-based force smoothing kernel to the linear theory $P(k)$. Use this as a secondary benchmark alongside the Quijote non-linear reference. This allows for the quantification of the "force softening" effect inherent to the PM algorithm, distinguishing between expected algorithmic behavior and actual simulation errors.

